* N: 1 *
********
**************
* RESPONSE 1 *
**************
The American novelist who won the Nobel Prize in Literature in 1954 was Ernest Hemingway. He was awarded the prize for his mastery of the art of narrative, most notably in his novella *The Old Man and the Sea*.

The contest in California that pays homage to him is the International Imitation Hemingway Competition (also popularly known as the Bad Hemingway Contest). This parody writing contest was established in 1977 by Mark S. Gross and was originally held at Harry's Bar & American Grill in Century City, Los Angeles. The competition invited participants to write a single page of very bad prose in the style of Ernest Hemingway, and the prize was often a trip to Italy to dine at the original Harry's Bar in Venice, a favorite haunt of the author.

Finish[International Imitation Hemingway Competition]
